{"metadata":{"title":"Instance Methods","role":"collectionGroup","roleHeading":"API Collection","modules":[{"name":"Tuplé"}]},"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"","text":""},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Some of the functions in this package should be considered “instance methods”. If tuples were a named type, we could extend them with real methods that incorporate dot syntax.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, to add 1 to a tuple of integers, we’d "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"like","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" to be able to write:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let tuple = (1, 2, 3)","tuple.map { $0 + 1 }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"…but the best we can do is:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["map(tuple)() { $0 + 1 }"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"heading","level":4,"anchor":"Recommended-Mental-Model-for-Tuple-Instance-Methods-Unsugared-Instance-Methods","text":"Recommended Mental Model for “Tuple Instance Methods”: Unsugared Instance Methods"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Say that we want to use "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swift\/collection\/map(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" on an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Int Array"},{"type":"text","text":". Because "},{"code":"Array","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a named type, Swift provides that functionality using this syntax:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["[1, 2, 3].map { $0 + 1 }"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"But this is sugar for what’s really going on. Swift’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"instance"}]},{"text":" methods are actually ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"type"}]},{"type":"text","text":" methods, which accept an instance as their argument, and return a closure. We typically think of this closure as the instance method itself."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To illustrate this, here’s an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Array"},{"type":"text","text":" extension:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["extension Array {","  func method() { }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You’d normally call that using this syntax:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let instance = [1, 2, 3]","instance.method()"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"But it’s also available as a "},{"code":"static","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" method, on "},{"code":"Array","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and can alternatively be called like this:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["Array.method(instance)()"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"And although you’ll need to add a version of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"try"},{"type":"text","text":", if you actually want the following to compile, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"text":" from the standard library can similarly be called like so:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["Array.map(instance)() { $0 + 1 }"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"That’s how the package authors think about the functions cataloged below.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It’s unfortunately not possible to remove the “"},{"code":"()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"” before trailing closures without access to "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"real"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" instance methods. The limitation has been logged as a bug for years."}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/tuple-\/instance-methods"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"topicSections":[{"title":"appending","identifiers":["doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/appending(_:)-3mlku","doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/appending(_:)-3nv0z"]},{"title":"callAsFunction","identifiers":["doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/callAsFunction(_:)-10f8r","doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/callAsFunction(_:)-3v7uy","doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/callAsFunction(_:)-1c4ez","doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/callAsFunction(_:)-6gpno","doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/callAsFunction(_:)-6z4bu","doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/callAsFunction(_:)-22s3f","doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/callAsFunction(_:)-5ubp1","doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/callAsFunction(_:)-6mnp9"]},{"title":"map","identifiers":["doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/map(_:)-5ky43","doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/map(_:)-17ar9","doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/map(_:)-3ybcw","doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/map(_:)-5b624","doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/map(_:)-6u36y","doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tupl-\/map(_:)-7vvm9"]}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Functions that would be instance methods if tuples could be extended.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/xn--tupl-epa\/documentation\/Tuple-\/Instance-Methods"},"references":{"doc://xn--tupl-epa/documentation/Tupl-/callAsFunction(_:)-1c4ez":{"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Call a 2-tuple of functions on one input."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"callAsFunction"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":